        "movement_why": {
          "text": "Pull-ups and push-ups are foundational bodyweight movements building vertical pull and horizontal push strength. Hollow body holds between sets reinforce midline tension, a prerequisite for all gymnastics movements. This combination develops coordination and body control under fatigue. The 21-15-9 rep scheme is a classic CrossFit descending ladder creating psychological momentum as rounds get shorter.",
