          "text": "Horizontal pulling strength emphasized through barbell rows, a foundational back-building movement. Top set + back-off scheme allows peak intensity exposure (85%) followed by hypertrophy volume (70%), maximizing both neural and structural adaptations within a single session. The 15-minute EMOM metcon rotates through vertical pull, vertical push, and horizontal push, creating balanced upper body work capacity development.",
