          "text": "Handstand push-ups require integration of vertical pressing strength, balance, and midline stability. Hollow and arch holds develop active body tension, the foundation of all gymnastics movements. Without the ability to maintain rigid body position, gymnastics skills cannot be performed safely or efficiently. The metcon combines vertical pull (pull-ups), vertical push (ring dips), and horizontal push (push-ups) for balanced upper body development.",
          "source": "Sommer - Building the Gymnastic Body",
